Section 1:
Act 213 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1450
4
5 By: Representative Painter
6 By: Senator Hill
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING REPORTS BY THE
10 DEPARTMENT OF AGRICULTURE; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
11
12
Subtitle
13
14 TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING REPORTS BY
15 THE DEPARTMENT OF AGRICULTURE.
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
18
19 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 2-16-310 is repealed.
20 2-16-310. Annual report.
21 The State Plant Board shall make an annual report to the Governor, in
22 which report it shall give an account of the disposition of the
23 appropriations which may be made for the purposes of carrying out the
24 provisions of this subchapter.
25
26 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code § 6-18-2103(d), concerning the annual report
27 prepared by the farm to school and early childhood education program
28 coordinator, is repealed.
29 (d) The farm to school and early childhood education program
30 coordinator shall:
31 (1) Prepare an annual report, in collaboration with
32 stakeholders, that details the program activities conducted in furtherance of
33 the following three (3) core elements of the farm to school and early
34 childhood education program:
35 (A) School gardens;
36 (B) Food, nutrition, and agriculture education; and
*CRH128*
02/11/2025 12:43:25 PM CRH128
HB1450
1 (C) Procurement of local farm or food products for school
2 meals and snacks; and
3 (2) Submit the annual report to the House Committee on
4 Agriculture, Forestry, and Economic Development and to the Senate Committee
5 on Agriculture, Forestry, and Economic Development.
6
7 SECTION 3. Arkansas Code § 15-23-1002(e)(2), concerning the annual
8 review and report on the Buffalo River Watershed Management Plan by the
9 Buffalo River Conservation Committee, is repealed.
10 (2) Conduct an annual review of the Buffalo River Watershed
11 Management Plan and include recommendations for updates of the plan and a
12 report on successes during the year, as identified by the committee, to be
13 submitted to the Governor;
14
15 SECTION 4. Arkansas Code § 20-60-217 is repealed.
16 20-60-217. Reporting.
17 Annually, the Secretary of the Department of Agriculture shall submit a
18 report on the operations, implementation, and administration of the State
19 Meat Inspection Program to the:
20 (1) Governor;
21 (2) Chair of the House Committee on Agriculture, Forestry, and
22 Economic Development; and
23 (3) Chair of the Senate Committee on Agriculture, Forestry, and
24 Economic Development.
25
26 SECTION 5. Arkansas Code § 25-38-203(a)(11), concerning the annual
27 report by the Department of Agriculture of the department's expenditures and
28 accomplishments provided to the Governor, is amended to read as follows:
29 (11) Prepare and submit annually to the Governor a report of the
30 Department of Agriculture’s expenditures and accomplishments activities and
31 programs, including information from all entities boards and commissions
32 administered by the Department of Agriculture;
33
34 SECTION 6. Arkansas Code § 25-38-203(a)(13), concerning the report by
35 the Department of Agriculture concerning certain boards and commissions, is
36 repealed.
2 02/11/2025 12:43:25 PM CRH128
HB1450
1 (13) Develop a report to be submitted each year on January 1 to
2 the Governor, the Senate Committee on Agriculture, Forestry, and Economic
3 Development, and the House Committee on Agriculture, Forestry, and Economic
4 Development, concerning the activities and programs of the:
5 (A) Arkansas Catfish Promotion Board;
6 (B) Arkansas Soybean Promotion Board;
7 (C) Arkansas Rice Research and Promotion Board;
8 (D) Arkansas Wheat Promotion Board;
9 (E) Arkansas Corn and Grain Sorghum Promotion Board; and
10 (F) Arkansas Beef Council.
11
12
13 APPROVED: 2/27/25
